texts.text: *Howl*
>The demons disappear and charms fall to the ground one by one...
I feel like we got a lot of them, but we just keep running into more.
We need to keep clearing them out then.
Check your six! Eyes in the back of your head!
All these obstacles are making this search and hunt...
So exciting...!
Why isn't there a gun that works against demons...?
Rika, then your demons would just start gathering dust.
>Nekomata, with a worried expression, keeps checking her surroundings...
Are you okay?
What's up?
Do I look okay?!
All these demons and there's no trace of her...
And no leads at all...
Didn't I say that I got separated from my sister?!
Please keep looking!
Wait, that part was true?
It wasn't just a way to lure us here...?
I'm not lying!!
I can't lie like you humans!!
I-It's not like we thought you were lying from the start.
But you think I'm lying now?
Uh, I mean... That girl's a human, right?
And you're a demon, so there's no way that you're her sister...?
Ugh! Forget it! I'm going on ahead!
But...
>Nekomata dashes off...
...Ririn, I think you went too far.
Yeah, I might've...
But wasn't it too hard not to ask? Anyone would've wanted to know...
I can't deny that... And I'm still wondering too.
She pleaded that much for our help, so it's hard to imagine she was lying.
...Please excuse her. She has a complicated past.
Oh, Kurama Tengu? Did something happen?
No. I'd also like to do what I can to find Saki.
I just happened to come by you is all.
So she really does have a human sister.
Of course, but they're not connected by blood.
...So the complicated past you mentioned has to do with this?
Yes, she's... In truth, she was not always a demon.
She was originally a cat. She lived long enough to gain the power to become a Nekomata.
That's actually possible?!
S-Sure, I've heard stories about cats living long enough to become Nekomata...
Indeed. We are the ones that helped her become the Nekomata you see today.
Could you tell us what happened?
...It starts with when she was still a cat.
Her first owner cared for her very much.
They did everything together and in time came to see her as his best friend.
Her owner even wished that he could converse with his cat.
She lived rather long and tried using the spiritual power she had accrued to grant his wish.
She slipped away from her home and came to this mountain.
She heard that there was a wise Tengu that called this mountain home,
and asked to be trained so that she could become a Nekomata.
Oh, that means...
Indeed, it is I.
She trained diligently and in time became a Nekomata...
Since she was able to grant her owner's wish, she returned home.
She thought that he'd be happy.
Hey, Bell...!

*Sigh*
Where is she? It's been weeks...
Oh, there you are! What are you doing...?
...Huh? W-What the hell are you...?
You can't tell? Well...
It's me! You're pet cat, Bell!
Surprised? How do I look?
I trained really hard and now I can talk...
D-Don't...
Hm?
Don't come closer, you monster!
...What?
There's no way you're Bell! She's just a regular cat!
B-But I trained so hard to become a Nekomata...
Don't come near me!
Hey...! Stop! Why are you throwing rocks at me? Listen...
There's no way she'd turn into a monster like you!
Go! I'm not falling for your lie!

*Pant*
Why... But he said.
"I wish you could talk"...
I just wanted him to be happy...
Liar...
Liar, liar!

*Sigh*
I can't... Stay like this much longer...
>Nekomata turned back into a cat...
Where am I...? I ran away without really thinking...
Whatever... I have nowhere to go and nowhere to call home now.
How did I end up all alone...?
If only I didn't think that I'd be able to talk to him too...
Maybe I could've just kept being a cat forever...
...It's getting cold.
...Hm?! A cat... What should I do...?
Mom! Dad! Come here!
That's so...
As Nekomata fell into death's grasp, a girl came and saved her.
After waking as a cat, she would claw, bite and rampage about.
She even escaped several times, but the girl always had her food and bed ready while looking for her.
The girl would cry every time she found her cat and Nekomata eventually gave in.
She decided to be this girl's pet.
Since then, 15 years have passed.
What?!
Saki is the daughter of the girl that saved Nekomata.
Nekomata has been with Saki ever since the day she was born.
Her "sister"...
But over 15 years have passed.
Nekomata has yet to tell Saki or her mother, her savior...
Not even once... Has she shown them what she actually is...
Oh, I see...
She understands how humans can be both affectionate and selfish.
She understands that as a cat, she will be loved.
And she experienced first hand that even the same person can be repulsed by her demon form.
She never really recovered from that one incident.
It hasn't mattered how much her new owner loved her as a cat.
She feels adamant that they won't be accepting of her Nekomata form.
But she wants to believe in Saki...
She's known her since she was born...
Humans... Some things about them we will never understand.
She may rough around the edges, but she is still my student. Please, help her.
Got it.
She's cute.
Words cannot express...
Ha, I wouldn't say that to her face if I were you. Unless you like being bitten.
Hey. I said hey! Why didn't you guys come after me?
None of you seem like the hiking type so...!
Don't come crying to me when you get lost!
...? Did I say something weird?
Oh, no. I'm sorry. Please, keep leading.
We need to find Saki as quickly as we can!
And. I'm sorry about earlier. I didn't mean to pry.
...! F-Forget it...
I deserve some of the blame since you're helping me out like this now...
Anyways! Let's go!
*Growl*
What should I do...? Why are there so many monsters around here?
I'm scared... I wanna go home...
But I still don't know where she went...
She might be scared and hiding somewhere too...
I can't give up now. I need to find her...!
Man, those things are everywhere...
Huh?
Oh.
W-W-Wait, don't scream. Please don't scream...!

*Scream*
Monster!!!!
>The girl collapses...
What?! Hey! Don't just scream and collapse on me!
Those things are gonna come here now!
We gotta get out of here...!
...Shit, this is bad!
Don't wake up! Please just stay asleep!
>Koppa Tengu flees and carries the girl deeper into the forest...
